https://github.com/helm/helm

Is the ntp setup properly already?

https://github.com/helm/helm/releases
Download your desired version
Unpack it (tar -zxvf helm-v3.0.0-linux-amd64.tar.gz)
Find the helm binary in the unpacked directory, and move it to its desired destination (mv linux-amd64/helm /usr/local/bin/helm)

From there, you should be able to run the client and add the stable repo: helm help.

kubectl get po --all-namespaces

hel pull name/name--untar=true

https://docs.gitlab.com/charts/

https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/charts/gitlab/-/blob/master/values.yaml
----
helm install monitoring ./kube-prometheus-stack


helm upgrade monitoring --values=myvalues.yaml .


kubectl get po

kubectl get svc
